Re: Breaking o u t w a r links <br>
<br>
It's a piece of cake.<br>
<br>
An admin goes to Community / Security settings / Profanity filter, and then enter in words that will automatically be filtered. Note that you do NOT have to enable the profanity filter in order to do this, the words you type in are above and beyond the standard filter.<br>
<br>
You then type in key parts of the links you want to break, for instance, I have O U T W A R in there (without the spaces, obviously), as well as any other siginifigent and unique parts of a link. For instance, for our buddy Yan tis, I have the webhost his referer system uses as well as the first part of the cgi script. For instance, I block &quot;mysuper sales&quot;, &quot;wetr ack&quot;, &quot;yant is&quot;, etc. Just type in all the words, seperated by commas, and it'll automatically break any links. It doesn't stop the spam, and the people that post it usually don't stick around long enough to even notice what happened, but at least they don't gain from the effort.<br>
<br>
Do note that the filter doesn't handle punctuation, for instance, if you want to block a script, like 'adspamlink.cgi', you would have to type in 'adspamlink'. If you type the whole thing out, then it doesn't block anything. Makes it a bit more complex when you have short cgi names (like say ad.cgi), since you can't really block the letters 'ad'. It's a bug, I've told and reminded EZBoard about it many times, and hopefully they'll fix it eventually.<br>
<br>
